        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"1611\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you want to make this simply, I would actually just implement a thin layer around RYWTransaction.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Would this be done through the C API, or are you recommending accessing RYWTransactions directly?</p>",
